Two weeks after a 67-year-old widow, Mrs Josephine Isiza, was burned beyond recognition by unknown hoodlums in Abavo, Ika North East Local Government area of Delta State, the police are yet to commence investigation as the state’s Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), DSP Onome Onovughagbogaya, said the command is not aware of the incident.
 
The Guardian gathered that the hoodlums carried out the act on October 9 at the deceased’s residence, the family home of Isiza in Abavo kingdom, which was also burnt down.
 
